269 (9) For purposes of revising or adjusting the ceiling
270 under Rule 560-X-22-.06(3) of the Alabama Administrative Code,
271 once the ceiling has been established for a fiscal year, it
272 shall be final and not subject to revision or adjustment
273 during that year, except as provided in this subdivision. At
274 the discretion of the agency, the ceiling may be revised or
275 adjusted upon either the discovery of a material error or upon
276 a determination by the commissioner that it is necessary to
277 increase one or more of the ceilings in the event nursing
278 facilities are unable to be reimbursed for increases in
279 allowable costs that were required to be expended by nursing
280 facilities to meet a nationwide or statewide public health
